Package: node-red-contrib-multiflexi
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, node-red (>= 4.0)
Description: Node-RED nodes for visual MultiFlexi process orchestration
 Manage relationships between MultiFlexi processes visually in Node-RED.
 The multiflexi-eventor daemon forwards webhook changes and finished jobs
 to these nodes, and flows schedule RunTemplates in response, turning the
 arrows you draw into orchestration logic.
 .
 Provided nodes:
  multiflexi-config      — MultiFlexi REST API connection (base URL + auth)
  multiflexi-event       — receives forwarded events over HTTP (the source)
  multiflexi-runtemplate — schedules a RunTemplate via POST /job/ (the target)
  multiflexi-artifact    — splits a job.completed event into per-artifact
                           messages for building processing chains
 .
 Optional X-MultiFlexi-Token header validation. Secret stored encrypted
 in Node-RED credentials.
